Hello,
I'm using gcc version 4.9.2 (i686-win32-dwarf-rev1, MinGW-W64) and it seems to optimize out the function "bool IsNaN(float value)". In the disassembly there is a "mov $0x0,%eax" and infact it always returns false.
Looking around I've found that it is a common problem with GCC >=4.8.1 with the flag -ffast-math. Using a volatile variable doesn't solve the problem. Just for the record, testing the correct bits like this:

```
bool IsNaN(float value)
{
    unsigned u = *(unsigned*)(&value);
    return (u & 0x7fffffff) > 0x7f800000;
}
```

_seems_ to work (and I'm good) but it is not portable at all for Urho.
